title: A Conversation with Olena Zelenska, the First Lady of Ukraine | Ukrainian Research Institute
snippet: In the words of HURI director Serhii Plokhii, Zelenska’s visit acknowledges HURI’s past five decades of achievements, and helps launch its journey “for the next 50 years.” · While visiting the Widener Library and meeting university librarian Martha Whitehead, the First Lady donated books to Harvard’s Ukrainica collection, which is the largest collection of Ukrainian material outside of Europe.
